# Montana State University
<!-- wss -->
<a href="projects/msu-masters/wss.qmd" style="text-decoration:none;">
  <span style="font-size:2em;">Master's Project</span>
</a>
  <span style="fonts-size:1em;">*wheat stem sawfly and native parasitoids*</span>  
<div class="box">  
Understanding the ecological importance of smooth brome (*Bromus inermis*) in biological control of the wheat stem sawfly (*Cephus cinctus*) using native parasitoids. 
<br>  
*PI: [Dr. David Weaver](https://landresources.montana.edu/directory/faculty/1524725/david-weaver){style="text-decoration:none;"}*
</div>
<br>
<!-- locoweed -->
<a href="projects/msu-masters/locoweed.qmd" style="text-decoration:none;">
  <span style="font-size:2em;">Locoweed Volatiles</span>
</a>
  <span style="fonts-size:1em;">*volatile profile differences in Oxytropis sericea*</span>  
<div class="box">  
Measuring the differences in volatile organic compound (VOC) profiles between *Oxytropis sericea* specimens containing the commensal endophyte *Alternaira oxytropos*, and those without.  
<br>
*PI: [Dr. Tracy Sterling](http://weedeco.msu.montana.edu/faculty/tracy_sterling/){style="text-decoration:none;"}*
</div>
<br>
<!-- toadflax -->
<a href="projects/msu-masters/toadflax.qmd" style="text-decoration:none;">
  <span style="font-size:2em;">Toadflax</span>
</a>
  <span style="fonts-size:1em;">*VOC data analysis*</span>  
<div class="box">  
Analyzing the difference in VOC profiles between two toadflax species and hybrids. Project in joint with the US Forest Service. 
<br>  
*PI: [Dr. David Weaver](https://landresources.montana.edu/directory/faculty/1524725/david-weaver){style="text-decoration: none;"} & [Dr. Sharlene Sing (USFS)](https://www.fs.usda.gov/research/about/people/ssing){style="text-decoration:none;"}*
</div>

